<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="288" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1210,2099,611,1230]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">• Mediumssized insectivores/omnivores, with stiff spines on head and back and relatively short rostrum (hedgehogs) or soft or coarse fur and shrew-like snout (gymnures).</paragraph>
